```
  {A, B, C}
 /       \
{B, D, E} {C, E, F}
 |         |
{B, D}   {C, F}
 |         |
{B, E}   {E, F}
   \     /
    {E, G}
```

In this tree decomposition, the largest set of vertices in any bag is {A, B, C}, which has a size of 3. Therefore, the treewidth of the graph is 3 - 1 = 2.
